cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.LG 

The paper deals with detecting misleading videos on YouTube, which involves analyzing the content of the videos and their metadata. This falls under the domain of multimedia analysis and computer vision (cs.MM, cs.CV). The authors also mention using text-based features to detect misleading metadata, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the problem of detecting fake videos can be seen as a cybersecurity issue, which falls under computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the authors propose a deep learning model for classification, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
